1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper is about people detection in images. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end model and introduces a new loss function. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses a recurrent LSTM layer for sequence generation. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a potential category as people detection is an important task for robots operating in crowded environments. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions non-maximum suppression, which is a common technique in object detection and can be used for security applications.
